features: DOMINATE THE SKIES: Give that aspiring pilot a reason to smile! Inspired by mega airliners, this 8.75"(L) x 10”(W) x 4"(H), airplane toy makes for hours of imagination-filled fun. Simply attach the wings and get the fun started.

COOL LED LIGHTS: At the slide of a switch, the fuselage and wings light up in red, green, and blue. Perfect for low-light fun, it’s just what you need to keep kids occupied even when the sun goes down. 3 x AA batteries are needed (not included).

REALISTIC SOUNDS: It’s not just the lights that will take the imagination to the next level. Our light up toy creates sounds that mimic engine & takeoff sounds. So, kiddos can really immerse themselves in pretend play.

BUMP ‘N’ GO ACTION: A spinning wheel at the bottom quickly moves the air plane toy across the floor. And whenever it bumps into an obstacle, it changes direction and continues with its wonder-sparking motion.

GREAT GIFT IDEA: Birthday, holiday, or anything in between, this LED toy airplane for boys and girls makes the perfect treat. It comes packed in a colorful box to inspire wonder at first glimpse. For ages 3+

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It works well !
reviews.reviewText: The Left and Right wings including those (3) at the fuselage came disassembled. You will need to snap these in first. Some trial and error are needed to properly connect these, but please do not force these in, as the plastic connecting clip (latch) may break. Only the body and the main wings are LED-lit. The engines do not. Not a bad deal for the price. The noise level is high and has no volume control.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fun enough for my toddler, but with a couple drawbacks
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This one is a bit difficult to rate...basically, I'm not a huge fan of this toy, but at the time of this review, it only costs about $10, which honesty, feels worth the price despite the faults. So, my review...What I like:• As mentioned earlier, price is great, and it's very competitive with other toys of this size and functionality.• The bump-and-go action is fun for my toddler (sort of like a Roomba).What I dislike:• This toy is super loud, and there is no volume control, so you're stuck with a cacophony of pain. The product states "realistic sounds," but it sounds more like a warzone.• This takes three AA batteries. Three of them. This is a fairly small toy, and I'm not sure how long my batteries will last (luckily, I am using rechargeable ones), but they are not included either.So again, by far, not a perfect toy, but you can't beat the price. Probably more accurate to say 3.5 stars though.
